  "texts": [
    "Aside from newer models being more expensive to run, their training data sets are more recent.",
    "For this research question, we wanted to ensure that the model had no prior knowledge of our cases (i.e., that these cases could not be present in its training data).",
    "We used OpenAI's native Python wrapper to execute our API calls.",
    "In selecting our cases, we first identified all cryptocurrency securities class action and SEC enforcement cases which were filed after June 2021 (and before our data collection date, on March 24, 2023).",
    "We included all SEC cases under the heading \"Crypto Assets\" on the SEC's Crypto Assets and Cyber Enforcement Actions page (U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission 2023)."
  ],
